{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17629283","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17629283"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:04:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:04:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17266"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17266","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17266"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9956"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78047"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9956","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9956"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17266"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63469"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4945"},{"type":"tags","id":"5725"},{"type":"tags","id":"10733"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23340"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23344"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78047","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78047"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ENext-generation sequencing technologies have revolutionised genomic research [1].\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the fundamental principle of next-generation sequencing?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Chemical degradation of DNA to determine base sequence","Direct visualization of DNA base pairs using electron microscopy","Parallel sequencing of millions of DNA fragments simultaneously","Sequential analysis of individual DNA fragments","Separation of DNA fragments by size using gel electrophoresis"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe fundamental principle of next-generation sequencing involves \u003Cstrong\u003Eparallel sequencing of millions of DNA fragments simultaneously\u003C/strong\u003E. This is achieved through massively parallel sequencing technology where multiple DNA fragments are sequenced at the same time on a single platform.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESequential analysis of individual DNA fragments\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes traditional Sanger sequencing, which analyzes one DNA fragment at a time\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirect visualization of DNA base pairs using electron microscopy\u003C/strong\u003E - While electron microscopy can visualize DNA structure, it cannot determine base sequence\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESeparation of DNA fragments by size using gel electrophoresis\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a DNA analysis technique but does not directly determine sequence\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChemical degradation of DNA to determine base sequence\u003C/strong\u003E - This refers to Maxam-Gilbert sequencing, an older method not used in next-generation sequencing\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe process typically involves library preparation (fragmenting DNA and adding adapters), cluster generation (amplifying fragments), and sequencing by synthesis (detecting incorporated nucleotides). This parallel approach allows for high throughput and reduced cost compared to traditional sequencing methods.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReferences:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E[1] Gu W, Miller S, Chiu CY. Clinical Metagenomic Next-Generation Sequencing for Pathogen Detection. Annu Rev Pathol. 2019;14:319-338.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Next-generation sequencing can sequence millions of DNA fragments simultaneously using massively parallel sequencing technology.","The key steps in next-generation sequencing are library preparation, cluster generation, and sequencing by synthesis.","Next-generation sequencing provides higher throughput and lower cost per base compared to traditional Sanger sequencing."],"references":["Turnpenny PD, Ellard S. Emery\u0027s Elements of Medical Genetics E-Book: Elsevier Health Sciences; 2011","Hu T, Chitnis N, Monos D, Dinh A. Next-generation sequencing technologies: An overview. Hum Immunol. 2021;82(11):801-811. doi:10.1016/j.humimm.2021.02.012.","Behjati S, Tarpey PS. What is next generation sequencing? Arch Dis Child Educ Pract Ed. 2013;98(6):236-8. doi:10.1136/archdischild-2013-304340."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63469"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17266"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63469","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63469"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-09T10:40:39+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-09T10:41:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9956"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78047"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading